Name: Chest Pain
Description: Discomfort or pain that you feel anywhere along the front of your body between your neck and upper abdomen.

Name: Shortness of Breath
Description: A feeling of not being able to breathe well enough.

Name: Fatigue
Description: Feeling overtired, with low energy and a strong desire to sleep that interferes with normal daily activities.

Name: Nausea
Description: A feeling of sickness with an inclination to vomit.

Name: Dizziness
Description: A sensation of spinning and losing one's balance.

Name: Headache
Description: Pain in any region of the head.

Name: Swelling
Description: An abnormal enlargement of a part of the body, typically as a result of an accumulation of fluid.

Name: Fever
Description: A temporary increase in your body temperature, often due to an illness.

Name: Cough
Description: A sudden, forceful hacking sound to release air and clear an irritation in the throat or airway.

Name: Memory Loss
Description: Forgetfulness, a condition in which a person experiences a persistent lack of memory.
